              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Four silicon detectors monitored continuously the",
                "beam intensity and position. The detected Ni-64 ions",
                "elastically scattered on the target. The detectors were",
                "placed above and below, and to the left and right of",
                "the beam at scattering angles 13-16 degrees."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SPEC",
                "PS"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Binary reaction products were detected by",
                "the two-arm time-of-flight spectrometer CORSET. Each",
                "arm of spectrometer consisted of a compact start",
                "detector and a position-sensitive 9*7 cm stop",
                "detector, both based on microchannel plates. The",
                "angular acceptance for both arms was (+ -12.5) degr.",
                "in-plane and (+ -10) degr. out-of-plane. The arms of",
                "the spectrometer were positioned at angles 60 degr. and",
                "-60 degr. to the beam axis."
              ]
